ing_topics.YAHOO_SCOUT\":\"Yahoo Scout\",\"trending_topics.AI_LEGAL_HOVER_TEXT\":\"Yahoo uses AI to summarise trending stories. Mistakes are possible.\",\"trending_topics.TOC_TITLE\":\"Trending stories\",\"trending_topics.UI_TOGGLE_SIMPLE\":\"Compact\",\"trending_topics.UI_TOGGLE_DETAILED\":\"Detailed\",\"trending_topics.METHODOLOGY_SECTION_TITLE\":\"Methodology\",\"trending_topics.METHODOLOGY_SECTION_BODY\":\"The stories that make up the Yahoo 100 ranking come from two different places. Some are drawn from the thousands of articles that are published across Yahoo each day, while others are based on social videos trending across Instagram, TikTok and Facebook. The stories are enhanced by the perspectives, judgements and human personalities of the writers and editors of the Yahoo newsroom.\",\"trending_topics.METHODOLOGY_SECTION_ARTICLE_LINK_TEXT\":\"To rank the storylines, we combine internal Yahoo data on article traffic and search trends with ‘lift’ metrics from social media. Then we use a large language model to help write the descriptions that help you make sense of it all.\",\"trending_topics.MILESTONE_RANKING_TEXT\":\"#{rank} trending story\",\"trending_topics.GOING_VIRAL\":\"Racking up views\",\"trending_topics.BIGGEST_JUMP\":\"Biggest jump\",\"trending_topics.FUN_STUFF\":\"Mood booster\",\"trending_topics.TOP_COMMENTED\":\"Driving conversation\",\"trending_topics.YAHOO_100_GREEN_SIGN\":\"Powered by Yahoo Scout\",\"trending_topics.YAHOO_100_YELLOW_SIGN\":\"Polished by people\",\"trending_topics.YAHOO_100_PURPLE_SIGN\":\"Don't miss\",\"trending_topics.ALL_STORIES\":\"All stories\",\"trending_topics.POWERED_BY_SCOUT_LINK_TEXT\":\"Powered by Yahoo Scout.\",\"trending_topics.POWERED_BY_SCOUT\":\"Yahoo is using AI to identify stories being covered and generate summaries from articles. This means the info may not always match what’s in the article.\",\"uvRadar.ADVICE_0\":\"There's zero to minimal ultraviolet radiation. It may be night, winter or very cloudy. Feel free to step outside sans sun protection.\",\"uvRadar.ADVICE_1\":\"You can safely spend time outside without sun protection. However, wearing sunscreen daily is recommended. Grab some SPF 15+ and go!\",\"uvRadar.ADVICE_2\":\"Low UV, low risk. SPF 15+ will suffice. But be careful: reflective surfaces like snow, sand and water can increase exposure.\",\"uvRadar.ADVICE_3\":\"When the UV hits 3, proceed with caution. Hat? Check. Sunglasses? Check. SPF 30+ sunscreen? Check. In midday, seek shade for bonus points.\",\"uvRadar.ADVICE_4\":\"Your sunburn risk is moderate. Grab polarised sunglasses, slather on SPF 30+ and wear a wide-brimmed hat and protective clothing.\",\"uvRadar.ADVICE_5\":\"The forecast is sunny with a side of caution. Seek shade between 10 a.m. and 4 p.m. and reapply SPF 30+ when outside.\",\"uvRadar.ADVICE_6\":\"Sun protection is vital. Fair-skinned people may burn in 20 minutes or less. Apply SPF 30+, seek shade and don't forget to hydrate.\",\"uvRadar.ADVICE_7\":\"Sun protection is key: hat, shades and long sleeves. When applying SPF 30+, don't skip your ears, eyelids, lips, scalp and feet.\",\"uvRadar.ADVICE_8\":\"We're in risky UV territory. Wear SPF 30+, sunnies, hat and loose-fitting long-sleeved shirts and pants. Stay inside if possible.\",\"uvRadar.ADVICE_9\":\"Sun safety is the name of the game. Avoid the outdoors midday as the shade can't fully protect you and cover up your skin.\",\"uvRadar.ADVICE_10\":\"In the high-risk UV zone, use the shadow rule: if it's shorter than you, head indoors or seek shade and always use maximum sun protection.\",\"uvRadar.ADVICE_11\":\"It's best to stay indoors, but maximum sun protection is a must if you're going out. Fair skin can burn in 5 minutes or less.\",\"uvRadar.TITLE\":\"UV index\",\"verticalVideo.TITLE\":\"Videos from Yahoo News\",\"verticalVideo.WATCH_VIDEO\":\"{title} - watch video\",\"weather.CANCEL\":\"Cancel\",\"weather.REAL_FEEL\":\"RealFeel® {real_feel_temp}°, {condition}\",\"weather.REAL_FEEL_S